hird of pregnant women suffer from clinical anxiety or depression.";i:4;s:68:"You naturally gain weight and your body normally changes during the.";i:5;s:62:"It is absolutely safe to use a massage chair during pregnancy.";i:6;s:96:"Many gynecologists even advocate the use of massage chairs and massage therapy during pregnancy.";i:7;s:97:"Of course there are some limitations to it which well discuss in the latter part of this article.";i:8;s:150:"Why Its Popular With Pregnant Women Chair massages are ideal for self-conscious pregnant women who dont want to lay on a table and who want to remain.";i:9;s:109:"This type of massage is typically oil or lotion-free so it may also be a good option for clients who have an.";i:10;s:33:"Chair massages usually only last.";i:11;s:78:"How to massage a pregnant client in a massage chair body positioning and more.";i:12;s:64:"Pregnancy Chair Massage Techniques taught by our amazing Brooke.";i:13;s:192:"Women with high-risk pregnancies pregnancy-induced hypertension or who have had previous pre-term labor should seek approval from their doctor before having chair or any other type of massage.";i:14;s:158:"The American Congress of Obstetricians and Gynecologists reports that back pain due to a growing uterus is one of the most common complaints during pregnancy.";i:15;s:55:"Chair massage is very safe for all stages of pregnancy.";i:16;s:54:"It is very useful for the second and third trimesters.";i:17;s:74:"The first trimester is very risky and adds the possibility of miscarriage.";i:18;s:80:"A pregnant woman can sit on a vibrating chair twice a day from 15 to 20 minutes.";i:19;s:40:"Massage Chair Benefits During Pregnancy.";i:20;s:192:"Research has shown that massage therapy during pregnancy can lessen anxiety improve symptoms of depression alleviate muscle aches and joint pains and enhance labor outcomes and newborn health.";i:21;s:78:"Though there are different techniques used the favored one is Swedish Massage.";i:22;s:178:"Some massage chair manufacturers recommend that pregnant women not use these chairs because of a concern that stimulating pressure points on the back could cause premature labor.";i:23;s:48:"But theres no evidence that supports this claim.";i:24;s:86:"Your baby is wrapped in many layers of muscle and fluid which keep her well cushioned.";i:25;s:40:"Why Using Massage Chairs Is A Good Idea.";i:26;s:78:"Here are some reasons why using massage chair during pregnancy is a good idea.";i:27;s:60:"The vibrating massage chairs work wonders to ease back pain.";i:28;s:103:"According to studies a massage chair helps circulate blood in the upper body relieving pain and cramps.";i:29;s:269:"Using a massage chair during pregnancy provides relief from leg and back pain which happens because the growing uterus requires a lot of space and exerts pressure on the bodyA massage chair can help circulate blood in the upper area of your body and thus ease the pain.";i:30;s:104:"Massage chairs have been used to help with this although some people have reservations about the chairs.";i:31;s:72:"There have been speculations that massage chairs can cause miscarriages.";i:32;s:87:"If you plan to use a massage chair while pregnant here are some things you should know.";i:33;s:51:"Concerns About Using Massage Chairs While Pregnant.";i:34;s:188:"The Specific Dangers of Mechanical Massage Chairs During Pregnancy One chief concern is elevated temperatures inside the womb that may cause heart rate spikes especially in smaller babies.";i:35;s:190:"Most mechanical massage chairs have a heating element or wand device that transfers heat to relax muscles and reduce the build-up of lactic acids and other proteins that form after exertion.";i:36;s:83:"Learn how to seat and position a pregnant client for optimal massage in a chair ma.";i:37;s:74:"Brooke does it again in this final part of our pregnancy massage tutorial.";i:38;s:188:"Chair massage for pregnancy A lot of zero-gravity chairs have a mechanism that per